# MERN Backend (Login API)

Backend server for Flutter login system.
Built with Node.js, Express, and MongoDB.

## 🛠 Tech Used
- Node.js
- Express
- MongoDB
- Mongoose
- CORS

## 🗄 MongoDB Commands (Windows)

Start MongoDB:
   net start MongoDB

Stop MongoDB:
   net stop MongoDB

Check Status:
   sc query MongoDB

## ▶️ Setup

1. Install dependencies:
   npm install express mongoose cors

2. Start MongoDB:
   net start MongoDB

3. Run server:
   node server.js

Server runs on:
http://localhost:3000

## 📌 API

Create user (run once):
GET /create

Login:
POST /login
{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "1234"
}

Returns:
{ "success": true/false }